Marcellite Garner https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marcellite_Garner 0 Edna Marcellite Garner (; July 3, 1910 – July 26, 1993) was an American artist and voice actress. She is most remembered as the first regular voice of Minnie Mouse during her time working at Walt Disney Productions and has been partially credited with defining Minnie's personality.
